Historical attribution
----------------------

The earliest scaffolding of this extension was forked from
robotframework-recorder v0.7.0
(https://github.com/viadee/robotframework-recorder), which was itself
a fork of Robotcorder (https://github.com/sohwendy/Robotcorder) by
@sohwendy. Both upstreams are licensed under GPL-3.0.

As of story RECORDER-LICENSE (2026), the five modules carrying the
upstream's substantive code — `src/locator/{scanner,classifier,
tree-builder,xpath-locator}.js` and `src/translator/robot-translator.js`
— have been re-implemented from scratch by viadee Unternehmensberatung
AG without reference to the GPL-3 source. The remainder of the
extension (background.js, content.js, popup.js, service-worker.js,
roboscope-client.js, actions-view.js, options.js, context-menu.js,
intro.js, keyword-spec.js, logger.js, …) was written for RoboScope
and has never carried upstream code.

The rewrite preserves the public API surface exercised by the existing
test suite, so callers (the extension's own background / content
scripts, plus the test files in `test/locator/` and `test/translator/`)
continue to work unchanged. No source line from the GPL-3 ancestors
remains in this directory.

The original authors are credited here as the inspiration that bootstrapped
the project; the implementation that ships in this version is original
work under the Apache-2.0 license:

  - @sohwendy           — Robotcorder (upstream of upstream)
  - @xylix              — robotframework-recorder / Robocorp Recorder
  - viadee Unternehmensberatung AG

